esiss_activities:
The index on page 32 gives  the page numbers for different topics in the book. 
Which page would you look at if you wanted to know:
&bull; how horses talk;
&bull; the jobs that horses do;
&bull; how to ride a horse.
Write three new entries for the index.

If Jack could see your home, he would be amazed at what electricity can do. In your own words, write an explanation for Jack, telling him how these items work:
&bull; a TV;
&bull; a garage door;
&bull; a toaster.

Write a report about a cephalopod, such as a squid, an octopus, or a nautilus.
Write about:
&bull; what the cephalopod looks like;
&bull; what it eats;
&bull; how it escapes from its enemies;
&bull; how it catches its prey,
&bull; any other special features.

It's important that people try to save energy. Design a poster for your class to explain how they can use less energy.
Be sure to include:
&bull; a catchy heading;
&bull; ideas on how to save energy;
&bull; facts about energy;
&bull; a labelled diagram showing things that use less energy.

Design a logo or an icon for the Incan people. It could be a shield or a flag that shows the important things in Incan culture. Use symbols and pictures to show:
&bull; the three main values that guided the Incas's lives;
&bull; the kind of land they lived on;
&bull; their homes and statues.

Use information from the book to write a police report about a crime.
Include:
&bull; what  happened;
&bull; the clues that were found;
&bull; how the crime was solved;
&bull; what happened after the crime was solved.

Head lice is a common parasite. 
Design a poster that gives information about head lice (nits).
Include:
&bull; a title;
&bull; a labelled diagram of a head lice;
&bull; facts about head lice;
&bull; how to avoid getting head lice;
&bull; how to get rid of head lice.

Brainstorm the ways that our world will change when oil runs out. In writing, explain:
&bull; how this will change the way we live;
&bull; how we will get around if we don't have petrol;
&bull; how it will affect the countries that produce oil.

The family in this book take part in a reality TV show. Create an idea for a TV reality show. Include:
&bull; the location;
&bull; the rules;
&bull; the contestants that would take part;
&bull; the challenges.
Show the idea to your family. Would they like to take part in your show?

Design an advertisement for a sea kayaking tour.
Include:
&bull; a catchy title;
&bull; a map;
&bull; highlights of the trip;
&bull; the duration and the cost.

Find a world map on the Internet or in an atlas. Using information from the book, find the following places on the map:
&bull; the Chinese cities, Beijing and Shanghai;
&bull; countries that people from China emigrated to; 
&bull; countries that border China;
&bull; countries that the Silk Road travels through.
